  "summary": "Bitcoin closes ~$58,620 on July 1, 2026, resolving July 10 (9-day horizon). Downtrend regime with mild bearish drift; Monte Carlo median ~$57,300, wide fat-tailed distribution reflecting crypto volatility and crisis-cascade downside risk.",
  "reasoning": "Forecast submitted.\n\n**Bitcoin price on July 10, 2026 \u2014 numeric forecast:**\n\n- **Median: ~$57,300** (down slightly from July 1 close of $58,620)\n- **10th\u201390th percentile: $52,400 \u2013 $62,800**\n- **P1: $47,800 | P99: $68,600**\n\n**Reasoning:** BTC closed at ~$58,620 on July 1, 2026, giving a 9-day horizon. The market is in a clear downtrend \u2014 it broke below $60K key support (now resistance), the Fear & Greed Index sits at extreme fear (15), and 20-day drift is -0.44%/day. I built a Monte Carlo simulation from 29 days of empirical returns (daily vol ~2.0-2.2%), using a mildly bearish drift center (dampened from the noisy raw estimate) with wide parameter uncertainty and Student-t(4) fat tails to capture crypto's leverage-cascade downside risk (analysts cite $44-53K targets if support fails) and oversold-bounce upside. Both tails are wider than a pure random walk to reflect the active crisis regime.",
